      <abstract id="aspace_d69248c0403d95d4f952de871628967c">The Institute for Computer Research in the Humanities was formed at New York University's University College in 1965, when a need developed for a method of organizing research and criticism in the humanities. Founders of the Institute aimed to eliminate an unproductive boundary between the humanities and technology in an attempt to advance scholarly research.</abstract>
